Target function 3D plot in Google

Newton function

f <- function(x,y) (x-2)^4+(x-2*y)^2

fx <- function(x,y) 4*(x-2)^3+2*(x-2*y)

fy <- function(x,y) -4*(x-2*y)

Newton method

max_iter <- 1000
alpha    <- 0.01

x0 <- c(0,3)

X <- c(x0[1])
Y <- c(x0[2])
for(i in 1:max_iter){
  
  f0 <- f(x0[1],x0[2])
  
  x0[1] <- x0[1] - alpha*fx(x0[1],x0[2])
  x0[2] <- x0[2] - alpha*fy(x0[1],x0[2])
  
  X <- c(X,x0[1])
  Y <- c(Y,x0[2]) 
  
  f1 <- f(x0[1],x0[2])
  
  df <- abs(f0-f1)
  
  if(df<=10^(-8)){
    cat(i, "th iter", "\n")
    cat(" x1 =", x0[1], "\n", 
        "x2 =", x0[2], "\n",
        "min =", f(x0[1],x0[2]), "\n")
    break
  }else if(i==max_iter){
    cat(i, "th iter", "\n")
    cat(" x1 =", x0[1], "\n", 
        "x2 =", x0[2], "\n",
        "min =", f(x0[1],x0[2]), "\n")
  }
}
## 1000 th iter 
##  x1 = 1.903451 
##  x2 = 0.9515554 
##  min = 8.701115e-05
plot(X,Y)

steepest descent function

fxx <- function(x,y) 12*(x-2)^2+2

fyy <- function(x,y) 8

fxy <- function(x,y) -4

fyx <- function(x,y) -4

H <- function(x,y) matrix(c(fxx(x,y),fyx(x,y),fxy(x,y),fyy(x,y)), ncol=2)

inv <- function(X){
  det <- X[1,1]*X[2,2]-X[2,1]*X[1,2]
  h <- c(X[2,2],-X[2,1],-X[1,2],X[1,1])/det
  X <- matrix(h,2,2)
  return(X)
}
gradf <- function(x,y){
  g <- c(fx(x,y),fy(x,y))
  grad <- matrix(g,2,1)
  return(grad)
}

steepest descent method

max_iter <- 1000

x0 <- c(0,3)

X <- c(x0[1])
Y <- c(x0[2])
for(i in 1:max_iter){
  
  f0 <- f(x0[1],x0[2])
  
  dxy <- inv(H(x0[1],x0[2])) %*% gradf(x0[1],x0[2])
  x0[1] <- x0[1]-dxy[1]
  x0[2] <- x0[2]-dxy[2]
  
  X <- c(X,x0[1])
  Y <- c(Y,x0[2]) 
  
  f1 <- f(x0[1],x0[2])
  
  df <- abs(f0-f1)
  
  if(df<=10^(-8)){
    cat(i, "th iter", "\n")
    cat(" x1 =", x0[1], "\n", 
        "x2 =", x0[2], "\n",
        "min =", f(x0[1],x0[2]), "\n")
    break
  }else if(i==max_iter){
    cat(i, "th iter", "\n")
    cat(" x1 =", x0[1], "\n", 
        "x2 =", x0[2], "\n",
        "min =", f(x0[1],x0[2]), "\n")
  }
}
## 14 th iter 
##  x1 = 1.993149 
##  x2 = 0.9965745 
##  min = 2.202975e-09
plot(X,Y)

Target function 3D plot in Google

Newton function

f <- function(x,y) sin(x^2/2-y^2/4)*cos(2*x-exp(y))

fx <- function(x,y) x*cos(x^2/2-y^2/4)*cos(2*x-exp(y))-2*sin(x^2/2-y^2/4)*sin(2*x-exp(y))

fy <- function(x,y) (-y/2)*cos(x^2/2-y^2/4)*cos(2*x-exp(y))+exp(y)*sin(x^2/2-y^2/4)*sin(2*x-exp(y))

Newton x0=(0.1,0.3)

steepest descent function

fxx <- function(x,y) cos(x^2/2-y^2/4)*cos(2*x-exp(y))-x^2*sin(x^2/2-y^2/4)*cos(2*x-exp(y))-4*x*cos(x^2/2-y^2/4)*sin(2*x-exp(y))-4*sin(x^2/2-y^2/4)*sin(2*x-exp(y))

fyy <- function(x,y) (-y^2/4-exp(2*y))*sin(x^2/2-y^2/4)*cos(2*x-exp(y))-1/2*cos(x^2/2-y^2/4)*cos(2*x-exp(y))-y*exp(y)*cos(x^2/2-y^2/4)*sin(2*x-exp(y))+exp(y)*sin(x^2/2-y^2/4)*sin(2*x-exp(y))

fxy <- function(x,y) (x*y/2+2*exp(y))*sin(x^2/2-y^2/4)*cos(2*x-exp(y))+(x*exp(y)+y)*cos(x^2/2-y^2/4)*sin(2*x-exp(y))

fyx <- function(x,y) (x*y/2+2*exp(y))*sin( x^2/2-y^2/4)*cos(2*x-exp(y))+(y+x*exp(y))*cos( x^2/2-y^2/4)*sin(2*x-exp(y))

H <- function(x,y){
  df <- c(fxx(x,y),fyx(x,y),fxy(x,y),fyy(x,y))
  h <- matrix(df,2,2)
  return(h)
}

inv <- function(X){
  det <- X[1,1]*X[2,2]-X[2,1]*X[1,2]
  h <- c(X[2,2],-X[2,1],-X[1,2],X[1,1])/det
  X <- matrix(h,2,2)
  return(X)
}
gradf <- function(x,y){
  g <- c(fx(x,y),fy(x,y))
  grad <- matrix(g,2,1)
  return(grad)
}

steepest descent x0=(0.1,0.3)

max_iter <- 1000

x0 <- c(0.1,0.3)

X <- c(x0[1])

  f0 <- f(x0[1],x0[2])

  x0[1] <- x0[1]-dxy[1]
  x0[2] <- x0[2]-dxy[2]

  }
}
